(2796, 1, '2018-08-23 11:23:12', '2018-08-23 11:23:12', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nMemo to: Vega Capital clients\r\nFrom: Scott Shuttleworth\r\nSubject: Vega’s 2nd month of returns\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<em>Neither the information, nor any opinion, contained on this Website constitutes a solicitation or offer by Vega Capital Pty Ltd (“Vega Capital”) or its affiliates to buy or sell any securities, futures, options or other financial instruments. Decisions based on information contained on this Website are the sole responsibility of the visitor whom we would encourage to seek relevant advice from a licenced professional.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Over the past week we have been overhauling the site layout and adding new content prior to the launch of the fund. If you experience any issues viewing or using our website, please don’t hesitate to let us know. </em>\r\n\r\nOver the Fund’s 2<sup>nd</sup> month of trading, the strategy generated a 2.4 per cent return. The portfolio was largely flat until we saw profits from Italy’s economic and political woes rising (again) followed by a strong unemployment number out of the US. President Trump’s imposition of trade tariffs were a detractor but a minor one at that.\r\n\r\nOur benchmark (the S&amp;P500 total return index) generated a 3.3 per cent return hence beating the Vega Fund’s performance by 0.9 per cent. This is not an unusual occurrence for the fund over short term time horizons – sometimes the index does run ahead. However over the medium term and longer term, the Vega fund has a strong tendency to catch up as shown in the back test results.\r\n\r\nVega’s active risk book generated a 5.9 per cent return whilst our hedging book detracted 3.5 per cent, largely due to front month June VIX futures falling from 15.6 to 13.35.\r\n\r\nCumulatively since inception, the strategy is up 5.77 per cent.\r\n\r\nThe Vega Fund will be formally opened on the 1<sup>st</sup> of July 2018 to sophisticated and wholesale investors. Our information memorandum and application forms will be posted on the website shortly.\r\n\r\nIf you are interested in becoming a foundation investor of the Vega Fund, please contact us at the link above.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em>Vega Capital is a Corporate Authorised Representative (No. 001264482) of Alpha Securities Pty Ltd (ACN 124 327 064) AFS Licence No. 330757.</em>', 'Vega’s 2nd month of returns – 2.4 per cent', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2576-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-08-23 11:23:12', '2018-08-23 11:23:12', '', 2576, 'http://vegacapital.net/new/uncategorized/2576-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
