(2803, 1, '2018-08-23 11:26:26', '2018-08-23 11:26:26', '<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nMemo to: Vega Capital clients\r\nFrom: Scott Shuttleworth\r\nSubject: Vega\'s first month trading performance\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<em>Neither the information, nor any opinion, contained on this Website constitutes a solicitation or offer by Vega Capital Pty Ltd (“Vega Capital”) or its affiliates to buy or sell any securities, futures, options or other financial instruments. Decisions based on information contained on this Website are the sole responsibility of the visitor whom we would encourage to seek relevant advice from a licenced professional.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nNo blog for this week however we do wish to inform readers on the Vega Fund\'s first month of live trading performance. The Vega Fund is currently trading with capital provided by the founder and this will be the case until our formal launch date.\r\n\r\nOver the last month, The Vega Fund has generated a 3.3 per cent return. The active risk book contributed 5.2 per cent in performance with the hedging book detracting 1.9 per cent.\r\n\r\nThe S&amp;P500 total return index also generated a 3.3 per cent return.\r\n\r\nWe took advantage of a few volatile days to increase the duration of the portfolio at opportunistic prices. The hedging book was moderated slightly as our risk algorithms became marginally less cautious. Overall this was an uneventful month.\r\n\r\nThe Vega Fund is a long term strategy. 3.3 per cent for the first month is certainly pleasing, but negligible relative to performance over the long term.\r\n\r\nWe are currently in the final stages of agreements for administration, AFSL and other standard fund requirements. As such, we\'ve moved our launch date until the 1st of July 2018.<!-- <fw_preview_session>1525932334219</fw_preview_session> -->', 'Vega\'s first month trading performance', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2147-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-08-23 11:26:26', '2018-08-23 11:26:2